## What is a *smart pointer* 

Object that behaves as a pointer by overloading `operator*()`
and `operator->()`

===
=== topic

    // the most simple SmartPointer
    template <typename T>
    class SmartPointer
    {
        public:
            T* operator->()
            {
                return m_Pointer;
            }

            T& operator* ()
            {
                return *m_Pointer;
            }
        private:
            T* m_Pointer;
    };

===
